library(readr)
WDIData <- read_csv("/Users/macbook/Documents/university/term6/data analysis/HW/hw_10/WDI_csv/WDIData.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   `Country Name` = col_character(),
##   `Country Code` = col_character(),
##   `Indicator Name` = col_character(),
##   `Indicator Code` = col_character(),
##   X63 = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
WDISeries <- read_csv("/Users/macbook/Documents/university/term6/data analysis/HW/hw_10/WDI_csv/WDISeries.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
data=bind_cols(WDIData[,1:3],WDIData[,43:62])  
series=WDISeries[c(1:3)]
data_merged=merge(data,series)
#baraye inke nemudar kheili shulugh nashe chand ta keshvar entekhab shode
countrylist=c('Iran, Islamic Rep.','Germany','France','Russian Federation')
final=data_merged %>% filter((str_detect(Topic,'Economic') & str_detect(Topic,'Policy'))==TRUE) %>% 
  filter(`Country Name`%in% countrylist)

final=final %>% 
  group_by(`Country Name`) %>% 
  select(-`Country Code`,-Topic,-`Series Code`)

final= gather(final,key="year",value="val",3:22)
final=final %>% arrange(final$`Indicator Name`)
indicator=final[,1] %>% distinct()

for (i in c(1:20)) {
final$check=(final$`Indicator Name`==indicator$`Indicator Name`[i])
temp=final %>% filter(check==TRUE)
temp=temp %>% arrange(year)
hc<-temp %>% hchart("line",hcaes(x=year,y=val,group=`Country Name`))
print(hc)
}

۶. در قسمت قبل با استفاده از روش خوشه بندی k-means داده ها را به سه دسته تقسیم کنید. ایران در کدام دسته می گنجد؟ (پیش از خوشه بندی طبیعتا داده را باید پاکسازی و استاندارد سازی نمایید.) 

#miangin 20 meyar ra be onvan e roshd e eghtesadi dar nazar migirim

data=bind_cols(WDIData[,1:3],WDIData[,43:62])  
series=WDISeries[c(1:3)]
data_merged=merge(data,series)
final=data_merged %>% filter((str_detect(Topic,'Economic') & str_detect(Topic,'Policy'))==TRUE)

final=final %>% 
  group_by(`Country Name`) %>% 
  select(-`Country Code`,-Topic,-`Series Code`)

indicator=final[,1] %>% distinct()

for (i in c(1)) {
final$check=(final$`Indicator Name`==indicator$`Indicator Name`[i])
temp=final %>% filter(check==TRUE)
listdata=list(temp)
}


for (i in c(2:20)) {
final$check=(final$`Indicator Name`==indicator$`Indicator Name`[i])
temp=final %>% filter(check==TRUE)
listdata[[i]]=temp
}

test=listdata[[1]]
#normalize
test[,c(3:22)]=scale(test[,c(3:22)])
#remove NA
test[is.na(test)]<-0

for (i in c(2:20)){
test2=listdata[[i]]
test2[,c(3:22)]=scale(test2[,c(3:22)])
#remove NA
test2[is.na(test2)]<-0
test[,c(3:22)]=test[,c(3:22)]+test2[,c(3:22)]
}

kcl=kmeans(test[,c(3:22)],centers = 3)
print('Iran is in group:')
## [1] "Iran is in group:"
kcl$cluster[210]
## [1] 2

test$label=kcl$cluster
pca = prcomp(test[,c(3:22)])
data=data.frame(x=pca$x[,1],y=pca$x[,2],color=kcl$cluster)

۱۰. کشورهای دنیا را بر حسب ۶۰ شاخص اقتصادی، سلامت و آموزش با روش سلسله مراتبی خوشه بندی کرده و دندروگرام آن را رسم نمایید. اگر داده ها بر سه دسته تقسیم شوند ایران در کدام دسته می گنجد؟ 

data=bind_cols(WDIData[,1:3],WDIData[,43:62])  
series=WDISeries[c(1:3)]
data_merged=merge(data,series)
final=data_merged %>%
  filter(((str_detect(Topic,'Economic') & str_detect(Topic,'Policy')) | ((str_detect(Topic,'Education')))
          |((str_detect(Topic,'Health'))))==TRUE)

final=final %>% 
  group_by(`Country Name`) %>% 
  select(-`Country Code`,-Topic,-`Series Code`)

indicator=final[,1] %>% distinct()

for (i in c(1)) {
final$check=(final$`Indicator Name`==indicator$`Indicator Name`[i])
temp=final %>% filter(check==TRUE)
listdata=list(temp)
}


for (i in c(2:60)) {
final$check=(final$`Indicator Name`==indicator$`Indicator Name`[i])
temp=final %>% filter(check==TRUE)
listdata[[i]]=temp
}

test=listdata[[1]]
#normalize
test[,c(3:22)]=scale(test[,c(3:22)])
#remove NA
test[is.na(test)]<-0

for (i in c(2:60)){
test2=listdata[[i]]
test2[,c(3:22)]=scale(test2[,c(3:22)])
#remove NA
test2[is.na(test2)]<-0
test[,c(3:22)]=test[,c(3:22)]+test2[,c(3:22)]
}

#clstering
dist = stats::dist(test,method = "euclidean")
dist %>% as.matrix() %>% image()

clus = hclust(dist,method = "complete")
plot(clus)

hcut= cutree(clus,k=3)
print('Iran is in cluster:')
## [1] "Iran is in cluster:"
hcut[210]
## [1] 2
